de.hshl.obj.data.array

Class FloatVectors

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.hshl.obj.data.array.FloatVectors

  • public final class FloatVectors
extends java.lang.Object
    Growable array of float vectors, stores components in interleaved fashion (x0,y0, x1,y1, x2,y2). Each FloatVectors instance has a fixed dimension, meaning it can only ever contain exclusively for example 3-dimensional or 2-dimensional vectors, and not both at the same time. Terminology: Vectors are groups of Coordinates. Methods expecting Vectors will throw exceptions if the dimensions are incorrect.
    Author:
    Johannes Vollmer
    See Also:
    IntegerVectors
